# Apps Script Web App URL
#
# This file should contain a single line with your deployed Apps Script URL.
# Do NOT commit the real URL to git -- it's gitignored for security.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Open Google Apps Script: https://script.google.com
#   2. Create a new project and paste the contents of ../apps-script-code.js
#   3. In the Apps Script editor, go to Services > add "Drive API" (v3)
#   4. Deploy > New deployment > Web app
#      - Execute as: "User accessing the web app"
#      - Who has access: "Anyone within [your org]"
#   5. Copy the deployment URL and save it to this file (without the .example extension):
#      cp apps-script-url.txt.example apps-script-url.txt
#      echo "https://script.google.com/a/macros/yourorg.com/s/YOUR_DEPLOY_ID/exec" > apps-script-url.txt
#
# If a teammate has already deployed the Apps Script, ask them for the URL.
# Since it's deployed with "Anyone within the organization", all org members can use the same URL.
